Avoiding NPE when a DefineMorphShape does not define start or end shape edges. This addresses SDK-29037.

Fix SDK-28982 by modifying the error message for an invalid character or markup in MXML. MXMLC's interface compiler was incorrectly assuming that this sort of scanner error would occur inside <fx:Script> blocks. Also updating the three scanner-related errors reported by MXMLC to include line and column information as this will greatly help the developer locate the problem.
QE notes: Please update any unit tests to cater for the new error message formats.
